Quote:  The miner, quickly recognising these characters, uses them in his search for ore-bodies, and calls any rock exhibiting them `favourable' or `kindly' country. ... The cause of the ore is the cause of the `favourable' country, and it is not correct to say that `favourable' country (in the sense used by the Hauraki miners) is the cause of ore-deposition. place in New Zealand during Captain Cook's first visit in 1769.
